### **Template Method Design Pattern for Sorting Algorithms**

#### **1. Abstract Class `SortAlgorithm`**

```java
public abstract class SortAlgorithm {
    // Template Method
    public final void sort(int[] array) {
        for (int i = 0; i < array.length - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < array.length - i - 1; j++) {
                if (compare(array[j], array[j + 1])) {
                    swap(array, j, j + 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Abstract Methods to be implemented by subclasses
    protected abstract boolean compare(int a, int b);
    protected abstract void swap(int[] array, int i, int j);
}
```

#### **2. Concrete Subclasses**

##### **a. `BubbleSort`**

```java
public class BubbleSort extends SortAlgorithm {
    @Override
    protected boolean compare(int a, int b) {
        return a > b; // Ascending order
    }

    @Override
    protected void swap(int[] array, int i, int j) {
        int temp = array[i];
        array[i] = array[j];
        array[j] = temp;
    }
}
```

##### **b. `SelectionSort`**

```java
public class SelectionSort extends SortAlgorithm {
    @Override
    protected boolean compare(int a, int b) {
        return a > b; // Ascending order
    }

    @Override
    protected void swap(int[] array, int i, int j) {
        int temp = array[i];
        array[i] = array[j];
        array[j] = temp;
    }

    // Override sort() for Selection Sort logic
    @Override
    public void sort(int[] array) {
        for (int i = 0; i < array.length - 1; i++) {
            int minIndex = i;
            for (int j = i + 1; j < array.length; j++) {
                if (compare(array[minIndex], array[j])) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }
            if (minIndex != i) {
                swap(array, i, minIndex);
            }
        }
    }
}
```

